    clinicalExplanation: "Body fluid balance depends on the interplay between intake, output, and hormonal regulation (ADH, aldosterone, ANP). Electrolytes — particularly sodium, potassium, calcium, and magnesium — are critical for cellular function, cardiac conduction, muscle contraction, and acid-base balance. Imbalances can result from inadequate intake, excessive losses (GI, renal, third-spacing), hormonal dysfunction, or medication side effects. Understanding the relationship between electrolytes and their clinical manifestations enables nurses to anticipate problems and intervene before life-threatening complications develop.",
