    introduction: "Clinical scenario practice is the bridge between theoretical knowledge and real-world nursing practice. By working through realistic patient situations, nursing students develop the critical thinking, prioritization, and clinical judgment skills essential for both licensing exams and clinical competence.",
    clinicalExplanation: "Effective clinical scenario practice requires a systematic approach mirroring the nursing process and the NCSBN Clinical Judgment Measurement Model. Follow this framework: First, identify the relevant cues. Second, analyze cues by grouping related data and identifying abnormals. Third, prioritize using ABCs, Maslow hierarchy, and assessment before intervention. Fourth, generate evidence-based solutions. Fifth, take action by selecting the most appropriate intervention. Finally, evaluate outcomes. Common scenario themes on nursing exams include: multi-patient prioritization, delegation decisions, emergency response sequencing, medication safety decisions, and ethical dilemmas.",
